The video, filmed during a student protest at Jomo Kenyatta University of Agriculture and Technology, close to the capital, Nairobi, has been widely shared on social media. People have been commenting on it using the hashtag #StopPoliceBrutality. In response, the police chief said: "We commend the individual who had the presence of mind to record the incident and thank all Kenyans who made it go viral."

